    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="768"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/338.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Vice President of the Whitney-Central
                            National Bank of New Orleans</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Solicitor
                            for the Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Orleans</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to our conversation on the subject of the $500,000 temporary loan to
                    Honduras—in which you suggested that any differences pertaining to the loan
                    agreement should be arbitrated by one selected by the Bank and one by the
                    Republic, with the Secretary of State as umpire—President Bonilla cables as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>We would accept as supreme arbitrator the President of the Supreme Court
                            of Justice of the United States of America.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please wire me if, after consultation with Mr. Knox and others, in your opinion
                    this would have the same effect as if arbitrator were the Secretary of State,
                    and if it will furnish us all of the safeguards which you stated would be
                    furnished under this plan. Please answer by wire at our expense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sol Wexler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
